review_blob: Light amber colour. Caramel and apple nose. The flavour is a mix of caramel parred with a hoppy bitterness that feels quite unusual. A good ale.
Cloudy golden colour and a white head. Aroma is like putting your face in a wet pine branch. Flavour is grapefruit, pine and lots of hops. Well done and quite delicious.
Thick off-white head. Distinct smell of bunt sugar. Flavour is quite light but well balanced. Burnt sugar and some malt.
Fairly good sand brown head topping a dark roasted like brew. The nose is a mix of coffee, dark chocolate and some raisin. Flavour is some caramel and cocoa. Bitter and slightly sweet.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Hazy yellow colour with a large bubble head. uplifting fragrance of grass, lemon, yeast, cinammon and hay. Flavour is similar with grass, lemon and lime. Well balanced witl  a slight bitterness and a pleasant sour finish.
Hazy yellowish coulour with bubbly head and some yeast residues in the bottle. Quite fragrant with hints of lemon and coriander. Flavour yeasty, dry and fruity with an acidic finish. Sehr gut!
Beutifully golden with a thick long lasting head. A dry, somewhat malty flavour with some spice, yeast and a hoppy bitterness. Very good.
Deep amber colour with a brownish head. Malty, with caramel and brown sugar tones both in flavour and aroma.
Amber coloured brew with a nice ale type head that lingered till the end. Nose is a bit ligth with some bread and malt. Flavour is dry, lightly hoppy with tones of pine.
Ligthly golden with a with head fairly well lasting head. Malty with herb tones delightfully bitter. A great pils.

Looks a little tired... Pale golden coulour with a  head that disappeared way too quickly. The taste is rather sweet and malty and goes well with pork and sauerkraut as a beer like this should. Overall not as good as I remembered it from previous years.
Beutiful amber coulour with slight yeast sediments and a thick, long lasting head. Some grapefruit and pine, and a moderate bitterness makes it an ideal thirst quencher.
Great amber coulour with an OK head. Flavour is typical IPA but more malty than I prefer and it is not as well balanced I would have expected. The focus is on the finishing bitterness...

Nice light brown head. Brown sugar is the dominant bouqet. Flavour is as expected: Coffee, chocolate, sligthly bitter with a noticable alcohol taste that spoils the beer experience to some extent More interesting than good.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: A watery, uninteresting beer, with  thin to non existant head. I would say it  is only good for washing down the dust and grime you will feel in your throat after walking a day in one of Chinas poluted cities.
A great German Pilsner with good citrus and malt tones and a lasting bitterness.

Draught at The Rover, Gteborg.

Good pale brown head that lasted throughout the drink. A mouthwatering aroma, hinting at a, for a Brown Ale, unusual hoppiness and a lovely dry, slightly citrusy flavour with a refreshing bitterness.
